widgets_values: A dining room that epitomizes contemporary elegance, anchored by a sleek, minimalist dining table paired with stylish modern chairs. Artistic lighting fixtures create a focal point above, while the surrounding minimalist decor ensures the space feels open, airy, and utterly modern

Generates a guide image to be used as input for the IP Adapter.

- Can be generated using the `segmind/SSD-1B` model:  
  [https://huggingface.co/segmind/SSD-1B](https://huggingface.co/segmind/SSD-1B/blob/main/SSD-1B.safetensors)
- The model should be stored under `models/checkpoints` folder.  
- Alternatively, the user may provide a different model or a reference image.
I recommend target size in 512 or 768(using multiply of eight equal origial pipeline)

Uses the guide image with the [ComfyUI_IPAdapter_plus](https://github.com/cubiq/ComfyUI_IPAdapter_plus) custom node.

## Required Models

- **IP Adapter SD15**  
  Download from:  
  [https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/resolve/main/models/ip-adapter_sd15.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/models)  
  Save to (maybe you need to create the folder):  
  `models/ipadapter`

- **CLIP ViT-H Encoder**  
  Download from:  
  [https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/resolve/main/models/image_encoder/model.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/models/image_encoder)  
  Save to:  
  `models/clip_vision/`  
  ⚠️ Must be renamed to `CLIP-ViT-H-14-laion2B-s32B-b79K.safetensors` for the node to work, since advanced model loading is no longer supported and the repo is unmaintained.

   - The **attention mask used by the IPAdapter** plays a key role in **preserving style features** from the reference image. When a mask is provided, the adapter **constrains the style application to specific regions**, maintaining **style consistency** only where needed. It is inverted to preserve only the control items selected

This step uses depth information to guide image generation via ControlNet.

## Depth Estimation

- Uses the custom node [Depth Anything V2](https://github.com/DepthAnything/Depth-Anything-V2)
- This replaces the older Depth Anything model, offering improved results with no major changes required to the pipeline.

## ControlNet Model

- Download the original custom depth ControlNet model from:  
  [https://huggingface.co/spaces/MykolaL/StableDesign/blob/main/controlnet_depth](https://huggingface.co/spaces/MykolaL/StableDesign/blob/main/controlnet_depth/diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors)  
- Save it to:  
  `models/controlnet`  
  ⚠️ It is recommended to rename the file, as it uses the default name from the repository (`diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors`).

This step uses a segmentation map to guide image generation via ControlNet.

## ControlNet Model

- Download the segmentation ControlNet model from:  
  [https://huggingface.co/spaces/MykolaL/StableDesign/blob/main/own_controlnet](https://huggingface.co/spaces/MykolaL/StableDesign/blob/main/own_controlnet/diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors)  
- Save it to:  
  `models/controlnet`  
  ⚠️ Rename the file to avoid confusion, as it comes with the generic name `diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors`.

This step generates the final image using **Stable Diffusion 1.5 with inpainting**, guided by both depth and segmentation ControlNets.

## Base Model

- **Model:** [Realistic Vision V5.1 (Inpainting)](https://huggingface.co/SG161222/Realistic_Vision_V5.1_noVAE/blob/main/Realistic_Vision_V5.1-inpainting.safetensors)  
- Save to:  
  `models/checkpoints`

> ⚠️ A newer version exists, but no major improvements were observed.

## ControlNet Combination

- ControlNets are combined in this order:
  1. Depth
  2. Segmentation

> 🔁 Changing the order had any impact on results. Other approaches might help better match the original pipeline.


The original pipeline explicitly replaced the scheduler with `UniPCMultistepScheduler`:

from diffusers import UniPCMultistepScheduler

self.pipe.scheduler = UniPCMultistepScheduler.from_config(self.pip

This step performs an upscale of the image.

## Process Overview

1. **Upscaling:**  
   - The image from the previous step is upscaled using [**4xUltraSharp**](https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-UltraSharp).

2. **Downscaling:**  
   - The upscaled image is resized back to its original diffused resolution.

3. **Latent Refinement via Denoising:**  
   - This upscaled latent is passed through the **same U-Net**, using the **same CLIP embeddings** and **IP Adapter**.  
   - A **controlled denoising** process is performed using a **low number of steps** (e.g., 5) and a **moderate noise level** (`strength=0.5`), typically with a scheduler such as *Euler Ancestral* or *DPM++*.  
   - This step focuses on **refining imperfections**, especially around **inpainting mask borders** or **edge inconsistencies**, without significantly altering the image structure or composition.
